data.chText: 奇异的；虚幻的；梦幻般的
data.enText: so strange that it is more like a dream than reality

data.chText: 聚会开始呈现出虚幻、近乎梦魇般的气氛。
data.enText: The party began to take on an unreal, almost nightmarish quality.

data.chText: 许多人对婚姻生活抱有不切实际的憧憬。
data.enText: Many people have unreal expectations of what marriage will be like.
used to say that you like sth very much or that sth surprises you

example: an insubstantial mirage on the horizon

tr: contrived by art rather than nature
lacking in reality or substance or genuineness
not corresponding to acknowledged facts or criteria
being or seeming fanciful or imaginary
example: this conversation is getting more and more unreal
the fantastically unreal world of government bureaucracy
the unreal world of advertising art

value.def: If you say that a situation is unreal, you mean that it is so strange that you find it difficult to believe it is happening.

example.ex: It was unreal. Like some crazy childhood nightmare...
example.tran: 这不是真的，就像儿时的某个荒唐的噩梦一样。

example.ex: It felt so unreal to be talking about our son like this.
example.tran: 真不敢相信我们会这样谈论我们的儿子。

value.tran: 不真实的；怪异的；难以相信的

example.ex: To his surprise he didn't feel too weak. Light-headed certainly, and with a sense of unreality, but able to walk.
example.tran: 令他惊讶的是他并没有感到很虚弱。虽然的确感到头晕，并有点儿虚飘飘的感觉，但他还是能走的。

value.def: If you use unreal to describe something, you are critical of it because you think that it is not like, or not related to, things you expect to find in the real world.

example.ex: Almost all fictional detectives are unreal.
example.tran: 几乎所有小说中的侦探都是虚构的。

value.def: Some people use unreal to indicate that they like something very much.

example.ex: Oh, I can't explain it. It's just unreal. Everybody is so happy.
example.tran: 啊，我都没法形容。就是太棒了，每个人都很高兴。
